
Metadata extractor

Idea:
* extarct metda data from files (existing nepomuk:resource)
* take this info and search the inter for more details
* python plugins (easy to write) handle teh actual search.
* python plugins only create a simple dictionary (transformed into QVariantMap
* the c++ part have neopomuk pip eclasses, tha ttransform such QVarianTMap data into DMS calls

+ not working yet, but planned
* the list of available searchengines is pre-filterd by the supported types (based in the resource type)
* the user can select between serveral matches (currenbtly always teh first is used)
* nepomuk resource based fetching
* handle other types than pdf/odt and nbib:Publication

#################################################################
# Dependencies:
* Nepomuk
** with nbib.ontology ~ see end of README

* poppler (for pdf parsing)
* PySide for the python parts

#################################################################
# install to the system

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ../ -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=`kde4-config --prefix` -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=release
make
make install

and start via metadatafetcher <url to file or folder>
or via right click service menu in dolphin

#################################################################
# install necessary ontology
copy
nbib/nbib.trig
nbib/nbib.ontology

into
/usr/share/ontology/nie